<!--
  Reeflex decision-gate syslog decoder for Wazuh (COMMUNITY EXAMPLE, UNMAINTAINED).

  Source: reeflex-core SIEM telemetry (REEFLEX_SYSLOG_ENABLED=true) - RFC 5424
  syslog, APP-NAME "reeflex", MSGID decision|lifecycle|kill_switch, MSG = one-line
  JSON.

  Efficient by design: a single cheap prematch anchored on the static
  " reeflex <procid> <msgid> - " marker scopes the decoder to Reeflex lines only;
  every field is extracted by Wazuh's native JSON_Decoder (verdict, rule_id, verb,
  ability, axes.*, magnitude_count, session_id, agent_id, on_behalf_of, environment,
  mode, decision_latency_ms, reason, namespace, target_ref, params.*, srcip -
  the /v1/decide caller IP, named "srcip" so Wazuh GeoIP enriches it when a
  GeoLite2 database is configured - and the traceability keys decision_id,
  hold_id, envelope_hash, parent_decision_id, traceparent). No per-field regex
  to maintain: JSON_Decoder auto-decodes any additive field, so new keys map to
  data.* with no decoder change (join alerts on data.decision_id).

  v0.1.13 (audit enrichment - Attest evidence, additive, no decoder change):
  the reeflex-core AUDIT LOG (decisions.jsonl -- NOT this syslog stream, but
  documented here so operators bridging the audit file into Wazuh via a
  file-based log collector recognize the same field vocabulary) gained
  agent_id + action.target_system on every decision record, and a NEW event
  shape sharing the same JSONL stream: hold_resolution ("event":
  "hold_resolution", fields hold_id, resolution [approved|rejected|expired],
  decided_by, decision_id, resolved_ts) -- the AI Act Art.14 human-oversight
  evidence trail for a hold's approve/reject/expiry. If a hold_resolution
  record is ever forwarded over THIS syslog channel (e.g. a future SIEM-sync
  emitter), JSON_Decoder auto-decodes it identically -- data.event ==
  "hold_resolution" distinguishes it from a decision record (which carries
  no "event" key) with no decoder change required.

  Install: copy to /var/ossec/etc/decoders/ on the Wazuh manager, then
  `systemctl restart wazuh-manager`. Test with /var/ossec/bin/wazuh-logtest.
-->
<decoder name="reeflex">
  <prematch type="pcre2"> reeflex \d+ \S+ - </prematch>
  <plugin_decoder offset="after_prematch">JSON_Decoder</plugin_decoder>
</decoder>
